name: King Ranch Chicken Casserole I
author: Susan Wright
summary: This is just one of the many King Ranch recipes available. Everyone seems to love it and it's sooooooo easy. Its' especially good when served with Mexican Corn Bread.
ingredients: 1 (10 ounce) can diced tomatoes with green chile peppers
1 (10.75 ounce) can  condensed cream of chicken soup
1 (10.75 ounce) can  condensed cream of mushroom soup
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C
) Layer the chips in a 9x13 inch casserole dish
Combine the tomatoes, chicken soup, mushroom soup and onion
Pour half of mixture over chips
Layer the chicken pieces, half of the cheese and the remaining soup mixture
Bake at 300 degrees F (150 degrees C) for 20 minutes
Top with the remaining cheese and return to the oven until the cheese is melted
